headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey scored 10 of his 20 points in the final 4:23 as the Detroit Pistons pulled away down the stretch and beat the Philadelphia 76ers 102-94 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bey's late scoring surge helps Pistons top 76ers 102-94

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo loved the fact that he became Milwaukee's career scoring leader on a 3-pointer, so nobody can say he's just a dunker anymore.
headlines.shortLinkText: Giannis becomes Bucks' scoring leader in OT win over Nets

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 30 points and the surging Atlanta Hawks never trailed while beating the short-handed Cleveland Cavaliers 131-107 on Thursday night to clinch a spot in the Eastern Conference play-in tournament.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young leads surging Hawks past struggling Cavaliers 131-107

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan did everything he could to carry the Chicago Bulls to a much-needed victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan scores 50, Bulls rally past Clippers 135-130 in OT

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell scored 29 points and Rudy Gobert had 25 points and 17 rebounds as the Utah Jazz snapped a five-game losing streak with a 122-109 win over the Los Angeles Lakers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah snaps five-game skid with 122-109 win over Lakers
